{
  "doc_id": "14148",
  "text": "The HRM diversity assay was performed as previously described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, DNA from the gag-pol and env regions was amplified. The amplicons were used as templates for a nested polymerase chain reaction (PCR); the nested PCR step included a fluorescent dye that was incorporated into the amplified products. The samples were analyzed using a LightScanner instrument (Model HR 96, BioFire Diagnostics, Inc., Salt Lake City, UT), which heats the samples and measures the change in fluorescence associated with DNA duplex melting. The range of temperatures over which melting occurs is defined as the HRM score [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Six genomic regions were analyzed: GAG1, GAG2, POL, ENV1, ENV2, and ENV3 [CITATION_5] .",
